<td>~</td>
<td><i>stolen</i></td>
<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[stoʊlən]</span> (<i>stole</i> + <i>-en</i>)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i>tear</i></td>
<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[tɛər]</span></td>
<td>~</td>
<td><i>tore</i></td>
<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[tɔər]</span></td>
<td>~</td>
<td><i>torn</i></td>
<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[tɔːrn]</span> (<i>tor(e)</i> + <i>-n</i>)</td>
</tr>
</table>
</dd>
</dl>
<ul>
<li>Vowel change between base/<i>-en</i> and past forms and <i>-(e)n</i> suffixation:</li>
</ul>
<dl>
<dd>
<table>
<tr>
<td><i>draw</i></td>
<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[drɔː]</span></td>
<td>~</td>
<td><i>drew</i></td>
<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[druː]</span></td>
<td>~</td>
<td><i>drawn</i></td>
<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[drɔːn]</span> (<i>draw</i> + <i>-n</i>)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i>fall</i></td>
<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[fɔːl]</span></td>
<td>~</td>
<td><i>fell</i></td>
<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[fɛl]</span></td>
<td>~</td>
<td><i>fallen</i></td>
<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[fɔːlən]</span> (<i>fall</i> + <i>-en</i>)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><i>take</i></td>
<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[teɪk]</span></td>
<td>~</td>
<td><i>took</i></td>
<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[tʊk]</span></td>
<td>~</td>
<td><i>taken</i></td>
<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[teɪkən]</span> (<i>take</i> + <i>-(e)n</i>)</td>
</tr>
</table>
</dd>
</dl>
<ul>
<li>Vowel changes in base, past, &amp; <i>-en</i> forms:</li>
</ul>
<dl>
<dd>
<table>
<tr>
<td><i>swim</i></td>
<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[swɪm]</span></td>
<td>~</td>
